  "title": "Unit Trust",
  "description": "Is A Banking Product that pools funds from multiple investors into a collective investment managed by a professional fund manager.\r\n\r\nA type of investment vehicle where investors buy units representing a portion of the fund, giving them proportional ownership of the underlying assets. Unit trusts are typically open-ended, allowing investors to buy or redeem units at the funds net asset value (NAV), and provide diversification and professional management.\r\n\r\nComment\r\nUnit trust is unincorporated mutual fund that pass profits directly to investors rather than reinvesting in the fund.",
